        "mainbody": "'''Shams al-Ezai''' was a [[half-elven]] [[Sorcerer (kit)|sorcerer]] inhabiting [[Qudra]] in [[north Zakhara]] in {{Yearlink|1367}}.{{AQ-time}}",
        "Activities": "Shams worked as a ''[[Midani dictionary|qadi]]'' in the [[Qudra/Slave market|slave market]]. He ensured that the slaves were treated properly and that no free men or women were there against their will. He was assisted by a pair of [[hakima]]s whose ability to read the truth in others was put to use.\n\nHe also served the [[Studious Mamluk Society]] by providing magical assistance when needed."
